BtSddbServiceAttribute * BtSddbServiceRecord::Delete (  BtSddbServiceAttribute *  service_attribute  ) 
 

Delete deletes the passed service attribute from this service record and returns the service attribute following the deleted one or 0 if the deleted one was the last. The deleted element is also destroyed, so the passed pointer gets invalid.

Parameters:
service_attribute A reference to a pointer to a BtServiceAttribute that should be deleted. The pointer is set to 0 if the attribute was in this service record and could be deleted.
Returns:
A pointer to a BtServiceAttribute pointing to the service attribute following the one that was deleted.

0 The service attribute that has to be deleted was the last one or was not contained in this service record. Check service_attribute to distinguish these two cases.

const BtSddbServiceAttribute * BtSddbServiceRecord::GetAttributeById (  UINT16  service_attribute_id  )  const
 

GetAttributeById searches this service record for the existance of an attribute with the passed id. If so the attribute is returned, otherwise 0 is returned to inidicate that the attribute was not found in this service record.

Parameters:
service_attribute_id An UINT16 containing the unique id of an attribute, that should be retrieved.
Returns:
A pointer to a BtServiceAttribute containing the service attribute with the passed unique id.

0 The service attribute matching the passed unique id can not be found.

UINT32 BtSddbServiceRecord::GetMemorySize (   )  const [protected]
 

GetMemorySize is used by the service discovery database and returns the size of this service record, if it would be stored in the format the BT-Stack expects.

Returns:

BOOLEAN BtSddbServiceRecord::Insert (  const BtSddbServiceAttribute &  service_attribute,
const BtSddbServiceAttribute *  position = 0
) 
 

Insert inserts a new service attribute into this service record.

Parameters:
service_attribute A reference to a BtServiceAttribute that depicts the service attribute that should be inserted çnto this service record. The service record, that should be inserted is copied.
position A pointer to a BtServiceAttribute containing the address of the service attribute of this service record before which the service_attribute should be inserted. If the position has the value 0 the service_attribute is appended at the end.
Returns:
TRUE The insert operation was successfull.

FALSE The insert operation failed. The service attribute was not inserted.

BOOLEAN BtSddbServiceRecord::ReadFromMemory (  const void *&  memory,
INT32 &  memory_size
)  [protected]
 

ReadFromMemory is used to construct the BtServiceRecord from a memory block containing a service record. The format how this memory block has to be interpreted is defined by the is_service_search_result flag.

Parameters:
memory A pointer to void containing the start address of the memory block, where to read this service record from.
Returns:
A pointer to void containing the address within the passed memory block, where the read ended.

void * BtSddbServiceRecord::WriteToMemory (  void *  memory  )  const [protected]
 

WriteToMemroy is used by the service discovery database and it writes this service record to a memory location in the format the BT-Stack expects.

Parameters:
memory A pointer to void containing the start address of the memory block, where to write this service record to.
Returns:
A pointer to void containing the address within the passed memory block, where the write ended.
